{
  "stem": "19550.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But so the public at large were not restricted to the Jewish community in the services or, or the goods that they sold.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in the Jewish school, of course, the teaching language was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not coeducational.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had separate classes for boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, in the, in the state schools or the state-operated schools, it was, of course, again Hungarian of the teaching language.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But for the more orthodox element and not only the Hasidim, the spoken language of the house and the family language was usually Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It-- you could almost judge the degree of religiosity by the, the language that was spoken at-- in the house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were the Hasidim whose real mother tongue was Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then as you went, so to say, up the ladder of-- or down the ladder of relative religiosity, the Yiddish could sort of peter out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There would be occasional use or just a few words.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Until you got to be assimilated, who didn't know any Yiddish at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They may have understood some of it, because many of them would have had either a German education or knew German as a second language.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they would understand the Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But basically, you would almost judge the degree of the religiosity by the language used in the home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The structure itself is in existence when I last visited there maybe about five or six years ago.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the fence around it, which was really part of the structure and was a rather elegant sort of fence and gate built into it was gone.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The institution, the, the structure itself stood.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The interior apparently was virtually totally destroyed in, in the sense that it was beautifully hand-painted.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
